ids\nexisted since the time of removal of the gas disk, unlike the terrestrial\nplanets, this constraint on the width of the giant planet jump is valid\nregardless of whether the instability happened early or late. Hence, at this\nstage, assuming an early instability does not appear to provide any advantage\nin terms of the probabilistic reconstruction of the solar system structure.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 14 Jun 2016 12:45:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-08-03"}
